  <summary date="2021-11-17T16:37:30Z" status="Introduced in House">Documenting Adversarial Trade Aggression Act or the DATA Act

This bill requires the Department of Commerce to establish a China Economic Data Coordination Center within the Bureau of Economic Analysis.

The center must collect, synthesize, and report on specified Chinese economic data regarding developments in China's financial markets and U.S. exposure to risks and vulnerabilities in China's financial system.</summary>
